# Chapter 11 — The Shark Tank

*A client pitch is a dungeon where the boss doesn't have health bars. They have budgets. And the only way to deplete them is to hit them with the one thing they can't ignore: the undeniable truth.*

---

The boardroom of the client, *Apex Retail Group*, was located on the 42nd floor of a tower that looked down on Pinnacle Systems like it was a pile of Lego bricks. 

Juan dela Cruz adjusted his tie—a cheap one he’d bought at a stall in Pasay, but ironed so sharply it could probably cut through a budget proposal. He was standing in the lobby, his hands in his pockets, feeling the low hum of Rodel and Cynthia in his shadow.

