╚══════════════════════════════════════════╝
```

"Gentlemen," Victor said, sitting at the head of the table. "Pinnacle Systems. You have twenty minutes. We’ve already seen five other agencies today. Give me one reason why I shouldn't just build this system in-house."

Aldrich stepped forward, his remote in hand. "Mr. Tan, thank you. At Pinnacle, we don't just build systems. We build Ferraris."

He clicked the remote. 

The screen bloomed with the first slide—the masterfully designed engine diagram that Shadow Cynthia had created. 

Victor Tan leaned forward, his eyes narrowing. "That’s not a Ferrari, Mr. Santos. That’s a load-balanced, containerized architecture with a microservices backend. Where did you get this data?"

Aldrich blinked. He hadn't actually looked at the slides after Cynthia had 'finalized' them. He had expected the stock photos of sports cars. 

"Ah, well, our team... we believe in transparency," Aldrich stammered, his True Rank of 'D' flashing bright red. "Cynthia, why don't you walk Mr. Tan through the technicals?"

Cynthia stepped forward. She looked at the screen, saw the engine she had only dreamed of building, and felt a surge of energy. 

```
