Juan felt the Rank Up pulse through his body. Rank D. He was no longer at the bottom. He was in the middle of the stack.

Aldrich stood frozen, his bespoke suit suddenly looking very cheap. He looked at Juan, and for the first time, he didn't see an invisible worker. He saw a predator.

"You," Aldrich hissed as the executives left the room. "You think you’ve won? You’ve just put a target on your back on the 14th floor."

Juan didn't blink. He looked at Aldrich, then at the flickering red 'D' above the man's head.

"I’m a Rank D now, Aldrich," Juan said. "And according to the System, you’re currently unranked."

Juan walked out of the boardroom, followed by the real Cynthia, who was looking at him with a mix of awe and terror. 

The Phoenix had risen. And the shadows were just getting started.

